attic.intro:
It sure is dark in here... Hopefully no robots come out and scare us!

...Wait, I AM a robot! Well, good thing I'm a friendly one!
attic.question: How about a fitting trivia question? During the Halloween Party, what was the Pizza Parlor renamed to?

beach.intro: Why, if it isn't the Fair! So many fun decorations were in this party! But not only that, a glorious Color Vote was held during this time. So many penguins rallied for their choosing color, with two new colors eventually becoming available for purchase!
beach.question: Can you tell me what two colors won this vote?

answers: We wanted to celebrate ocean life
beacon.intro:
Wow, look at all the sea life inside the beacon! There's so much in there! How did they even get that pufferfish to glow?!

The Submarine Party was a fun one!
It also had a special meaning behind it...
beacon.question: So tell me, what was the reason that we decided to hold a Submarine Party?

berg.intro: Ah, the Puffle Party! This was a fun event, as we were able to adopt these fluffy friends for the first time! I wish I had one...
berg.question: Here's a True or False question: During this party, the white puffle's habitat was at the Ski Hill.

boiler.intro: These puffles certainly look like they're having a good time in here! Did you know that they belong to Aunt Arctic? Hopefully she knows that they're in here. I also hear that there's a secret in this room!
boiler.question: So on that note, which of these items can be obtained as a secret on the island?

boxdimension.intro: There's so many cookies in here! I bet I could eat them all! ...If I had a mouth, that is. Each room for the Puffle Party definitely shows off each puffle's unique personality!
boxdimension.question: But can you tell me a room that was NOT accessible during the Puffle Party?

boxstore.intro: There's so many boxes in this room! This shouldn't even be physically possible! This was, of course, for the April Fools Party! Lots of items could be obtained, including a special igloo!
boxstore.question: And speaking of igloos, which of these is NOT a real igloo?

cave.intro: There's not much to look at down here... Of all the rooms in the April Fools Party, this one doesn't have much going for it. But at least you can look at the fish passing by out the windows!
cave.question: Hey, that just gave me a trivia question! What's a mini-game that does not have Fluffy the fish in it?

cavemine.intro: Why are these puffles deep underground? Maybe they're here to watch these penguins dig for coins, or listen in on their conversations, or admire their different methods of digging.
cavemine.question: And speaking of that, which of these hard hats were recently released?

courtyard.intro: After a months-long effort, in July of 2023, the Dojo Courtyard was finally dug out. To celebrate the release of Card-Jitsu then, the Card-Jitsu Party was held!
courtyard.question: During that party, what was the Lighthouse decorated as?

answers: There are 4 mats in the Dojo
You can purchase Power Card packs
cove.intro: Care for some tea? Actually, I probably shouldn't have any liquid, since it might make me short-circuit. At least I can still enjoy the scenery here!
cove.question: How about some Card-Jitsu trivia? Which of these facts is NOT true of Card-Jitsu?

dance.intro: Woo-hoo! It's a dance party in here! Penguins had a blast at the Graduation Event, grooving to this awesome music! If only there was a DJ in here...
dance.question: Speaking of DJs, can you tell me the name of the island's very first DJ, who retired long ago?

dock.intro: YEE-HAW! The Western Party took the entire island by surprise, as party planners set it up seemingly out of nowhere! There were lots of free items to be obtained and fun to be had!
dock.question: It was so good, I don't even have a question relating to it! So instead, what room sits behind the Ski Lodge?

dojo.intro: What a nice-looking room! Just like most rooms in the Holiday Party, this just fills you with peace. And its definitely a relaxing atmosphere to play Card-Jitsu in!
dojo.question: Speaking of Card-Jitsu, what month in 2023 did it release in?

eco.intro: REALLY? They just HAD to place me here!? There's just two pumpkins! What kind of decoration is that?!
eco.question: Ugh... It's fine, I have a trivia question nonetheless. Who's the editor of the Club Penguin Times?

forest.intro: Wow, it's so green in here! There's so many huge plants, and even a full-size Leprechaun House you can go into! Except... I don't have a good trivia question prepared!
forest.question: Hmm... OH! I know! What is Bean Counters' secret game mode?

forts.intro: Woah, is that a store made of boxes over there? And what happened to the snow forts? They're boxes too! I guess this is typical for April Fools' parties.
forts.question: So, how about everyone's favorite propeller-wearing penguin- Rookie? What party did he first visit at?

icepond.intro: What a beautiful sky! Who would've thought that Aurora Borealis could be localized entirely within this room?
icepond.question: Related to one of the games here, what type of fish appears in Fluffy The Fish?

lighthouse.intro: What a pretty looking room! Nothing like playing some tunes in a giant tree, am I right? The pictures on the wall also look nice!
lighthouse.question: So, did you know the Music Catalog has a secret item? Can you tell me what it is?

lodge.intro: Ah... What a cozy room! What could be better than playing Find Four with friends, next to a giant Christmas tree, with a relaxing piano in the background?
lodge.question: During the Holiday Party, what was the currency that could be earned to purchase special items?

lounge.intro: We're in the control room for a submarine! Well, it's not a real submarine. It's just the Dance Lounge remodeled to look like one. This was, of course, done for the Submarine Party, with the Night Club receiving similar treatment!
lounge.question: How about a good ol' True or False question: The Night Club was completely flooded during the Submarine Party.

mine.intro: Watch your step! The entire floor is ice; a perfect skating rink for these white puffles! This was just one of the many habitats during the Puffle Party.
mine.question: Everyone knows PH, the island's puffle lover, but can you tell me what "PH" stands for?

mtn.intro: The Winter Party was held somewhat recently in November, though this particular room doesn't have that many decorations. However, Lavender could be obtained here during the party!
mtn.question: What iconic mini-game was released during this party?

answers: She wrote a lengthy newspaper article
She put a sticky note on the newspaper
oldboiler.intro:
That red puffle looks so cozy in that bed, albeit it must be a bit lonely in here. Why doesn't it join the puffles upstairs?

This reminds me of the time when puffles escaped from
the Pet Shop, hiding all over the island, and we had
to find them!
oldboiler.question: So, why don't you tell me... How did Aunt Arctic make the call for the island to search for the missing puffles, with Puffle Roundup's payment doubling?

party.intro: We're in the Leprechaun House! Feel free to relax by the fireplace or beat that bodhrán over there... But not until you've answered my trivia question!
party.question: During the St. Patrick's Day Party, what room had a giant pot of gold?

answers: As a game in the Pizza Parlor
party1.intro: We're in the Pizza Parlor oven! Hopefully my circuits can handle the heat, or I'll have to get out of the kitchen! This was to celebrate the launch of the new mini-game Pizza Oven, which was actually not an original idea!
party1.question: So, can you tell me how Pizza Oven appeared in the original Club Penguin?

pet.intro: These puffles sure are having a blast! This room appeared in the Puffle Party, which celebrated the ability to adopt puffles for the first time. Later down the line, a couple of unique types of puffles could be adopted, too!
pet.question: Which one of these puffles released with what party?

pizza.intro: The Valentine's Day Party was one of the island's very first events! Several rooms were beautifully decorated- including this one! But did you know this party was not the first time it was held?
pizza.question: That's right, can you tell me the year that the previously only Valentine's Party was held?

plaza.intro: Ah, the Earth Day celebration! So beautiful, so green, and it celebrated the opening of the Recycling Plant! I even hear it's Aunt Arctic's favorite event!
plaza.question: Looking at the Stage just gave me a trivia question! What's a play that, as of right now, has NOT been shown at the Stage?

rink.intro: I sure love me some bumper cars! This was one of the island's many activites during The Fair. And among those, who could forget the mini-games?
rink.question: Which of these was NOT a game from the Fair?

shack.intro: Who planted all this bamboo around the Mine Shack? And who took it down after the Card-Jitsu Party ended? Oh well, at least it makes for a peaceful setting.
shack.question: Since we're near the Mine, can you tell me where the Miners Helmet can be found?

ship.intro: Ah, I remember this! The Fair was primarily celebrated in recognition of Rockhopper's ship finally being repaired, and they sure did the deck up nice!
ship.question: Do you know what caused Rockhopper's ship, The Migrator, to crash in the first place?

shiphold.intro: Rockhopper sure keeps lots of things down here; Some of which he's kind enough to sell in his Rare Items catalog!
shiphold.question: Can you tell me what was the first year Rockhopper offered this catalog?

shop.intro: Look at me, I'm the cashier now! It's so spooky in here, too! Could I interest you in some Halloween clothing?
shop.question: No? You wanted a trivia question? Oh, fine. What type of item in the Penguin Style catalog costs the least?

sportshop.intro: Look at me, I'm the cashier- Hang on, didn't I say that already? Oh well, how about a related trivia question?
sportshop.question: What other room looks very similar to the Sports Shop?

tourhq.intro: WOAH! Is that... a clone of me?! What are you, some kind of imposter!? Oh? It only gives tour guide jobs? Can it do trivia like me? I don't think so!
tourhq.question: But enough of that. Here's a true or false question: Tour guides receive a higher monthly paycheck than agents.

village.intro: The Beta Party celebrated the opening of this island, one year ago! I remember it like it was yesterday. It brings theoretical tears to my hypothetical eyes...
village.question: Getting off-topic a bit, in what room can you see most of the island?

scripts: Sailin' the seas be the life for me
I be causin' a roarin' ruckus with ye!
ARRR! how be ye this fine day?
The fastest ship on the seas!
It be faster than a slippery squid
It be faster than a greased cannonball
It be faster than Rookie chasing a sandwich
And let me tell ye mateys, he be pretty fast!
This be the barrel where I keep me stinky cheese
And this also be a barrel of stinky cheese
And this barrel... stinky cheese too
Perhaps I have too much stinky cheese
That be a joke, HAR HAR HAR!
You can never have too much stinky cheese
No, there's no crow up here
It just be a strange name
Ahhh, that one gets me every time
There be a memory dear to me heart
It be the time I meet me best friend...
I was sailin' me ship for new lands
All kinds of adventures I be havin'
Avast! In the sea there be a strange sight
It be a piece of driftwood with a puffle atop it
And sped to save that puffle's life
Ay, he warmed to me like a clam to a shell
and now he be me first mate!
It be the Coins for Change parties
Ye be a fine and generous crew
and ye donate ya hard earned coins
T'is a fine thing ye be doing
Arrrr... ye think this be a tear in me eye?
Nay, just a bit of sea salt, mateys!
It be the time ye helped rebuild the Migrator
A lily-livered ice berg crashed into me ship!
The migrator sunk to the bottom of the bay, it did!
But ye really came through for me, mateys
Ye worked hard to salvage her from the depths
and finally the Migrator was rebuilt!
Of course those pesky crabs sunk it later
But ye helped me with those scallywags too!
Mateys! how about a pirate parade?
Up the ladder to the Crow's Nest!
Last one to the Beach be a wet fish!
and a bottle o cream soda!
AVAST this be the place for pirates!
Who be servin' the food in this place?
HAR HAR HAR I be jokin'
Play a sea shanty me matey!
ARR ye be a fine piano player!
Here be my favoritest sea song
WE BE A CREW OF PIRATES
WE DRINK BARRELS OF CREAM SODA
AND EAT TONS OF STINKY CHEESE
BUT THE THING THAT WE LIKE BEST
I be in the mood for squid pizza
What else ye want on it, mateys?
Do ye like these toppings, mateys?
Arr...these pizzas not be sittin' well
That be the best pizza I ever had!
I got a case o' the pizza toots
Now that's what I be callin' FAIR winds
It be these fish yar har har!
Arr she be a fine ship!
Me ship be full o' treasure for everyone!
It be the pirate's life for me
I be the CAPTAIN of me ship!
Find me key to open me quarters!
Me journal be in the Newsroom
Ye hard work on me ship be noted! Thank ye!
Aye me key be hidden on this island!
Have ye found the key to me quarters?
What ye all think of me Captain's Quarters?
I see ye be liking me Treasure Hunt
Watch where ye be aimin those snowballs!
We be settlin this score the old fashioned way...
YE BE RUEIN THE DAY YE MESSED WITH ME
This be the greatest snowball fight ever fought
ARR, I be playin hide and seek!
Hide n' Seek be a good game for pirates
It be makin' ye could at findin things
This be a good place for a story
Who be tellin this tale? Ye or me?
I swear on me beard this be true!
Can ye guess what happened next?
Ye won't believe what happened next
That be the end o' me tale!
Yarr harr! Ye be a fine bunch o' listeners!!
when a strange creature came upon me
and he smelled of the sea
his teeth were as BIG as a whale
AND HE BE LOOKIN' MIGHTY HUNGRY
I feared he was to eat me
can you guess what happened next?
It be a tangled mess o' seaweed
And in it YARR be hidin'
So me treasure be safe after all!
burying me treasure on a strange new island
a group of treasure huntin' flamingos came me way
I not be sharin' with the likes of them
ye never know when they be tellin' the truth
they promised loads of cream soda
just as I be drinkin' me cream soda
they made off with me treasure
left me with nothin' but me friend YARR
Good thing I had some coins hiddin' in me beard!
Tryin' to follow me treasure map
When I be seein' a tiny pirate parade
They be marchin' across the sand
And even be havin' stinky cheese
It be ants with little eye patches!
When I followed 'em to their anthill
I saw where they be gettin' the cheese!
It be comin' from me own Migrator!
So I parlayed with their queen
And they helped be find treasure!
But I had to leave them me cheese
And I be sailin' the seas
When I saw black sails off me port bow
It be lookin' like a pirate battle!
But I be hollerin' to the cap'n
We both be pirates lookin' fer loot!
So the cap'n and I find an accord
That be meanin' we make a deal
So we both be gettin' new treasure!
ARR! I be proud to be ye friend!
Make sure to claim me background
It be a fine picture of me! YAR HAR!
Me beard keeps me warm on me travels!
It be good for storing things too
and an extra pair o boots!
Yarr be keeping lookout at me ship
Yarr be right here beside me!
Me favorite animal be a puffle!
Pirates! What be ye favorite animal?
I likes pirate music that I can dance a jig to!
What be ye favorite sport mateys?!
Me favorite sport be a snowball fight
Arr what be ye favorite hobby?
Me hobbies be sailin' and treasure huntin'
Find me key to open me quarters!
Me journal be in the Newsroom
Farewell me hearties! I be leavin' now!
Me hearties! thanks for the fun!
This be time for me to go!

tour_questions.question: What is the orange puffles favorite snack?

Which of these games has a shark in it?

How many Find Four boards can be found in the Lodge Attic?
What color puffle can be seen jumping on top of a speaker in the Night Club?
How does the pink puffle play?

tours.attic: This is the Lodge Attic.|It has been used to store just about anything!|It also has more Find Four tables.
tours.beach: This is the Beach, home of the Lighthouse.|It is a great place to relax in the sun.|Sometimes you see the pirate ship docked here!
tours.beacon: The Beacon holds the Lighthouse spotlight...|...and a telescope that you can look through.|And if you thought penguins could not fly...|...you should try the Jetpack game on the right.
tours.berg: This is the Iceberg. It is a secret room.|In the distance you can see Club Penguin.|If you want to dive into the ocean depths...|...try out the Aqua Grabber!
tours.boiler: This is the Boiler Room.|It gives electricity and heat to the island.|Here you can read old editions of the newspaper.|It is a great way to learn about Club Penguin Journey.
tours.book: Here is the Book Room.|Click on the bookshelf to read something.|You can also play a game called Mancala.|It's a fun game, but difficult to learn.|Read How to Play Mancala before playing...|then play a few games to learn how it works.
tours.boxdimension: Welcome to the Box Dimension.|This mysterious place is the source of all boxes.|Please leave the laws of physics at the door.
tours.cave: Here we have the Cave, which has its own pool.|It also has windows to see underwater.|Wait a moment, and a crab may walk by.
tours.cavemine: Here we have the Mine Cave...|Many penguins mine the gold reserves down here.|So grab a hardhat and start digging!
tours.coffee: This is the Coffee Shop.|The coffee here is delicious!|You can also click the bag of coffee beans...|...if you want to play Bean Counters.
tours.courtyard: This is the Courtyard.|It was covered in snow for many moons!|Enter the Dojo and take the path of the Ninja.
tours.cove: This is the Cove!|It is a wonderful, secluded spot.|You can go swimming in the shallow water here.|Or, test your surf skill and catch some waves!
tours.dance: Welcome to the Night Club.|This is THE place for dance parties.|That green puffle on the speaker is called the Keeper...|He was gone for a short while recently...|So it's good to have him back!
tours.dock: Welcome to the Dock.|You can play Hydro-Hopper here.|Take a ride on a tube behind the speedboat.
tours.dojo: Here we are in the Dojo.|Learn to become a Ninja with Card-Jitsu.|Train and earn belts to progress.|Only the dedicated will succeed.
tours.eco: This is the Recycling Plant!|Throw your recycling into the Recycletron 3000...|...and turn rubbish into useful things!
tours.forest: Welcome to the Forest!|Go to the Cove by walking down those stairs...|...or take the top right path to the Mine Shack...|...and help out at the garden.
tours.forts: These Snow Forts are fun for snowball fights.|Click the snowball icon to throw one.|Over there is the Club Penguin Journey clock.|It shows the time in the Penguin Standard Time Zone.
tours.hiddenlake: Wow! This place is the Hidden Lake...|Where did all this treasure come from, I wonder?|And it looks like there's a door under the water...
tours.hideout: Welcome to the Ninja Hideout!|Only ninjas have access to this special room.|Here you will find the Martial Artworks catalog...|Where you can buy lots of ninja clothing and furniture.
tours.hq: This room... is top secret, I can not tell you what goes on in here.|Oh, wait we are all agents here.| This room is the Agents Headquarters.|You can get here through the Sports Shop.|Or, you can just use your spy phone.|Click on a TV to go somewhere.
tours.icepond: This is the Ice Pond!|Here, you can go ice fishing...|...or watch Fluffy the Fish grow big!
tours.lighthouse: This is the Lighthouse...|...the tallest building in Club Penguin.|Take a look at the pictures on the wall...|...or grab a new instrument and perform on stage.|Go upstairs to find the Beacon!
tours.lodge: The Ski Lodge is a great place to warm up.|Or, you can play Find Four with friends.|You can also visit the Ice Pond out the back door.
tours.lookout: Here we are in the Lookout.|This room has the best view of the island!|Be sure to check the room during events!
tours.lounge: This is the second floor of the Night Club.|It is called the Lounge.|The Lounge is great for relaxing after dancing.|There are also fun arcade games here!
tours.mine: This is the Mine.|Puffles like exploring tunnels...|... and sometimes get trapped inside.|They need your help to rescue them!
tours.mtn: If you like to sled, come to Ski Hill!|I guess it should be called Sled Hill.|Bunny Hill is for newcomers, Ridge Run is only for pros.|The drop is almost straight down!
tours.oldboiler: The Old Boiler is quite unusual.|Penguins seem to have found this room by accident.|Be sure not to walk into this room's boiler.
tours.pet: The Pet Shop is where you can adopt a puffle.|Puffles are animals native to Club Penguin.|They have different colors and personalities.|They all like penguins, and make great pets.
tours.pizza: This is the Pizza Parlor.|Come here to order the best pizza.|If you go into the kitchen...|...you can help make pizzas with the Pizzatron.|Also, serve pizzas by visiting the pizza oven!
tours.plaza: Greetings from the Plaza!|From here, you can visit the Pizza Parlor...|...watch a play at the Stage...|...or you can adopt a puffle at the Pet Shop.
tours.rink: Welcome to the Stadium, sports fans!|Take part in the action and start a game!|Or grab a snack and watch from the bleachers.
tours.shack: Welcome to the Mine Shack...|Home of the Mine and the Community Garden!|Help water the garden by throwing snowballs...|...into the green bucket.|Beside the beautiful tree is the Recycling Plant...|...where we use garbage to make useful stuff!
tours.ship: This is the pirate ship, the Migrator. Arrrr!|Rockhopper sails the seas in this ship.
tours.shiphold: This is the ship's cargo hold.|Due to the crash the Migrator has faced...|...Rockhopper couldn't put his loot here.|Hopefully he will next time!
tours.shipnest: This is called the Crow's Nest...|...where Yarr keeps a lookout.|You can get a great view...|...of the island!
tours.shipquarters: This is the Captain's Quarters!|Rockhopper spends a lot of time here.|Look at the corkboard for his photos!|Or, grab a friend and hunt for some treasure!
tours.shop: This is the Gift Shop.|You can buy clothes from the monthly catalog.|Colors and backgrounds can be bought as well.|Use coins you have earned from playing games.
tours.sportshop: Welcome to the Sports Shop.|Here, you can buy all sorts of sports equipment.|There's absolutely nothing behind the rightmost change room.
tours.stage: Welcome to the Stage. Tickets please!|Many different plays are performed here.|A new play is put on every month or so!|If you're interested in a job...|...actors, directors, and stage hands are needed!
tours.tourhq: This is the Tour Headquarters.|You can become a tour guide here...|...or go upstairs to view the island from the Lookout!
tours.town: Welcome to the Town Center!|This spot is the heart of the island.|From here, you can get coffee|...dance at the Night Club...|...or check out the Gift Shop for some accessories.
tours.underwater: BLUB! This place is Underwater...|Look at all the colorful fish and plants! And treasure!|This sure is unusual...
tours.village: Here we have the Ski Village.|There's the Ski Hill, Ski Lodge and the Sports Shop...|...where you can buy lots of different sports equipment!
tours.welcome: This is the Welcome Room!|This is often the first place you visit.|If Club Penguin Journey is having a party...|...this room is usually well decorated for it.
